olive oil
2 potato
3 clove garlic
1 sprig rosemary
40 g butter
2.5 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
1 packet Premium Fillet Steak
1 bag baby broccoli
1 bag green beans
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet Homestyle Gravy
1 packet pecans
½ packet Basic Sponge Mix
1 packet Dark Chocolate Chips
1 packet brown sugar
1 packet Caramel Sauce
2 pear
½ bottle cream
4 eggs
1 cup water

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Bring
a medium saucepan of lightly salted water to the
boil. Peel the potato and cut into large chunks.
Finely chop the garlic. Pick and finely chop the
rosemary (see ingredients). Cook the potato in the
boiling water until easily pierced with a fork,
10-15 minutes. Drain the potato. Return the
saucepan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook the rosemary and garlic until
fragrant, 1 minute. Add the potato, butter,
milk and the salt to the pan with the rosemary.
Remove from the heat, then mash until smooth.
Cover to keep warm.

See Top Steak Tips (below) for extra info!
While the potato is cooking, combine a drizzle of
olive oil and the Nan's special seasoning in a
medium bowl. Add the premium fillet steak and
turn to coat. In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of
olive oil over a high heat. Add the steak to the hot
pan and sear until browned, 1 minute on all
sides. Transfer to a lined oven tray. Roast for
8-10 minutes for medium or until cooked to your
liking. Remove the steak from the oven and set
aside to rest for 5-10 minutes.

While the steak is roasting, halve the baby broccoli
lengthways. Trim the green beans.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the diced
bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl. Return
the frying pan to a medium-high heat, then cook
the baby broccoli and green beans until softened,
5-6 minutes. Transfer the veggies to the bowl with
the bacon. Season.

While the steak is resting, wipe out the frying pan, then return to a low heat. Cook the homestyle gravy, stirring, until warmed through, 5 minutes.

Slice the premium roast beef. Divide the
rosemary-garlic mash and bacon greens
between plates. Top with the beef. Pour over
the homestyle gravy to serve.